2.1.1.37.1.7.2  container vnfr:guest-epa
  Leaves
    name: trusted-execution, type: BOOLEAN, description: This VM should be allocated from trusted pool
    name: mempage-size, type: ENUM, description: Memory page allocation size. If a VM requires
    hugepages, it should choose LARGE or SIZE_2MB
    or SIZE_1GB. If the VM prefers hugepages it
    should choose PREFER_LARGE.
    LARGE        : Require hugepages (either 2MB or 1GB)
    SMALL        : Doesn't require hugepages
    SIZE_2MB     : Requires 2MB hugepages
    SIZE_1GB     : Requires 1GB hugepages
    PREFER_LARGE : Application prefers hugepages
    name: cpu-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU pinning policy describes association
    between virtual CPUs in guest and the
    physical CPUs in the host.
    DEDICATED : Virtual CPUs are pinned to
      physical CPUs
    SHARED    : Multiple VMs may share the
      same physical CPUs.
    ANY       : Any policy is acceptable for the VM
    name: cpu-thread-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU thread pinning policy describes how to
    place the guest CPUs when the host supports
    hyper threads:
    AVOID   : Avoids placing a guest on a host
    with threads.
    SEPARATE: Places vCPUs on separate cores,
    and avoids placing two vCPUs on
    two threads of same core.
    ISOLATE : Places each vCPU on a different core,
    and places no vCPUs from a different
    guest on the same core.
    PREFER  : Attempts to place vCPUs on threads
    of the same core.
    name: numa-unaware, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:guest-epa
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:guest-epa
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/vdur/STRING/guest-epa
  RW Keyspec XPath Path

2.1.1.37.1.7.2.2  container vnfr:numa-node-policy
  Description
    This policy defines NUMA topology of the
    guest. Specifically identifies if the guest
    should be run on a host with one NUMA
    node or multiple NUMA nodes. As an example
    a guest might need 8 VCPUs and 4 GB of
    memory. However, it might need the VCPUs
    and memory distributed across multiple
    NUMA nodes. In this scenario, NUMA node
    1 could run with 6 VCPUs and 3GB, and
    NUMA node 2 could run with 2 VCPUs and
    1GB.
  Leaves
    name: node-cnt, type: UINT16, description: The number of NUMA nodes to expose to the VM.
    name: mem-policy, type: ENUM, description: This policy specifies how the memory should
    be allocated in a multi-node scenario.
    STRICT    : The memory must be allocated
    strictly from the memory attached
    to the NUMA node.
    PREFERRED : The memory should be allocated
    preferentially from the memory
    attached to the NUMA node
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:guest-epa/vnfr:numa-node-policy
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:guest-epa/vnfr:numa-node-policy
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/vdur/STRING/guest-epa/numa-node-policy
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:guest-epa/vnfr:numa-node-policy
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:guest-epa/vnfr:numa-node-policy
  Protobuf Type
    .vnfr.YangData.RwProject.Project.VnfrCatalog.Vnfr.Vdur.GuestEpa.NumaNodePolicy
  Python Proto-GI Type
    VnfrYang.YangData_RwProject_Project_VnfrCatalog_Vnfr_Vdur_GuestEpa_NumaNodePolicy

2.1.1.37.1.7.5  container vnfr:host-epa
  Description
    Specifies the host level EPA attributes.
  Leaves
    name: cpu-model, type: ENUM, description: Host CPU model. Examples include: SandyBridge,
    IvyBridge
    name: cpu-arch, type: ENUM, description: Host CPU architecture.
    name: cpu-vendor, type: ENUM, description: Host CPU Vendor.
    name: cpu-socket-count, type: UINT64, description: Number of sockets on the host.
    name: cpu-core-count, type: UINT64, description: Number of cores on the host.
    name: cpu-core-thread-count, type: UINT64, description: Number of threads per cores on the host.
    name: om-cpu-model-string, type: STRING, description: OpenMANO CPU model string

2.1.1.37.1.7.7  list vnfr:volumes
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name for the volume configuration
    name: device-name, type: STRING, description: Device-name of the disk eg. vda, vdb etc
    name: volume-id, type: STRING, description: VIM assigned volume id
    name: preexisting-resource-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the preexisting volume in the VIM
    name: delete-on-terminate, type: BOOLEAN, description: Controls the deletion of preexisting volume in VIM
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description for Volume
    name: size, type: UINT64, description: Size of disk in GiB
    name: ephemeral, type: EMPTY
    name: image, type: STRING, description: Image name for the software image.
    If the image name is found within the VNF package it will
    be uploaded to all VIM accounts during onboarding process.
    Otherwise, the image must be added to the VIM account with
    the same name as entered here.

    name: image-checksum, type: STRING, description: Image md5sum for the software image.
    The md5sum, if provided, along with the image name uniquely
    identifies an image uploaded to the CAL.

    name: device-bus, type: ENUM, description: Type of disk-bus on which this disk is exposed to guest
    name: device-type, type: ENUM, description: The type of device as exposed to guest
    name: volume-type, type: STRING, description: Type of the volume
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:volumes
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:volumes[vnfr:name='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path

  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:volumes

2.1.1.37.1.7.8  list vnfr:internal-connection-point
  Description
    List for internal connection points. Each VNFC
    has zero or more internal connection points.
    Internal connection points are used for connecting
    the VNF components internal to the VNF. If a VNF
    has only one VNFC, it may not have any internal
    connection points.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: mac-address, type: STRING, description: MAC address assigned to the internal connection point
    name: connection-point-id, type: STRING
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:internal-connection-point
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:internal-connection-point[vnfr:id='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/vdur/STRING/internal-connection-point/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:internal-connection-point
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:internal-connection-point[vnfr:id='STRING']
  Protobuf Type

2.1.1.37.1.7.9  list vnfr:interface
  Description
    List of interfaces (internal and external) for the VNF
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the interface. Note that this
    name has only local significance to the VDU.
    name: position, type: UINT32, description: Explicit Position of the interface within the list
    name: preexisting-resource-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the preexisting port in the VIM
    name: delete-on-terminate, type: BOOLEAN, description: Controls the deletion of preexisting port in VIM
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the Interface
    name: internal-connection-point-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Leaf Ref to the particular internal connection point
    name: external-connection-point-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Leaf Ref to the particular external connection point
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:interface
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:interface[vnfr:name='STRING']

    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:vdur[vnfr:id='STRING']/vnfr:interface[vnfr:name='STRING']

2.1.1.37.1.7.9.1  container vnfr:virtual-interface
  Description
    Container for the virtual interface properties
  Leaves
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Specifies the type of virtual interface
    between VM and host.
    VIRTIO          : Use the traditional VIRTIO interface.
    PCI-PASSTHROUGH : Use PCI-PASSTHROUGH interface.
    SR-IOV          : Use SR-IOV interface.
    name: bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: Aggregate bandwidth of the NIC.
    name: ovs-offload, type: ENUM, description: Defines if the NIC supports OVS offload.
    MANDATORY : OVS offload support in the NIC is mandatory.
    PREFERRED : OVS offload support in the NIC is preferred.
    name: vendor-id, type: STRING, description: Specifies the vendor specific id for
    the device. This is used when a NIC from
    specific HW vendor is required.
    name: datapath-library, type: STRING, description: Specifies the name and version of the datapath
    library the NIC is expected to support.
    name: provider-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the provider network to which this
    NIC is attached.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:interface/vnfr:virtual-interface

2.1.1.37.1.7.10  list vnfr:placement-groups-info
  Description

      Placement groups to which this VDU belongs and its
      cloud construct
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.

    name: cloud-type, type: ENUM
    name: aws-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: mock-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: cloudsim-construct, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:vdur/vnfr:placement-groups-info
  XPath Keyed Path

2.1.1.37.1.10  list vnfr:placement-groups-info
  Description

      Placement groups to which this VDU belongs and its
      cloud construct
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.

    name: cloud-type, type: ENUM
    name: aws-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: mock-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: cloudsim-construct, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr:vnfr/vnfr:placement-groups-info

2.1.1.39.1.1.1  list nsr:connection-point
  Description
    List for external connection points.
    Each NS has one or more external connection
    points. As the name implies that external
    connection points are used for connecting
    the NS to other NS or to external networks.
    Each NS exposes these connection points to
    the orchestrator. The orchestrator can
    construct network service chains by
    connecting the connection points between
    different NS.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the NS connection point.
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:nsd/nsr:connection-point

2.1.1.39.1.1.2  list nsr:scaling-group-descriptor
  Description
    scaling group descriptor within this network service.
    The scaling group defines a group of VNFs,
    and the ratio of VNFs in the network service
    that is used as target for scaling action
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of this scaling group.
    name: min-instance-count, type: UINT32, description: Minimum instances of the scaling group which are allowed.
    These instances are created by default when the network service
    is instantiated.
    name: max-instance-count, type: UINT32, description: Maximum instances of this scaling group that are allowed
    in a single network service. The network service scaling
    will fail, when the number of service group instances
    exceed the max-instance-count specified.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:nsd/nsr:scaling-group-descriptor
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr[nsr:id='STRING']/nsr:nsd/nsr:scaling-group-descriptor[nsr:name='STRING']

2.1.1.39.1.1.2.1  list nsr:scaling-policy
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the scaling policy
    name: scaling-type, type: ENUM, description: Type of scaling
    name: enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Specifies if the scaling policy can be applied
    name: scale-in-operation-type, type: ENUM, description: Operation to be applied to check between scaling criterias to
    check if the scale in threshold condition has been met.
    Defaults to AND
    name: scale-out-operation-type, type: ENUM, description: Operation to be applied to check between scaling criterias to
    check if the scale out threshold condition has been met.
    Defauls to OR
    name: threshold-time, type: UINT32, description: The duration for which the criteria must hold true
    name: cooldown-time, type: UINT32, description: The duration after a scaling-in/scaling-out action has been
    triggered, for which there will be no further optional
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:nsd/nsr:scaling-group-descriptor/nsr:scaling-policy

2.1.1.39.1.1.11  list nsr:vld
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the VLD.
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Virtual Link Descriptor (VLD) name.
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: resource-name, type: STRING, description: VLD Name in VIM
    name: vendor, type: STRING, description: Provider of the VLD.
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description of the VLD.
    name: version, type: STRING, description: Version of the VLD
    name: type, type: ENUM
    name: root-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the aggregate bandwidth.
    name: leaf-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the bandwidth of branches.
    name: mgmt-network, type: BOOLEAN, description: Flag indicating whether this network is a VIM management network
    name: vim-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of network in VIM account. This is used to indicate
    pre-provisioned network name in cloud account.
    name: ip-profile-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Named reference to IP-profile object
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:nsd/nsr:vld

2.1.1.39.1.1.11.1  container nsr:provider-network
  Description
    Container for the provider network.
  Leaves
    name: physical-network, type: STRING, description: Name of the physical network on which the provider
    network is built.
    name: overlay-type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the overlay network.
    LOCAL - Provider network implemented in a single compute node
    FLAT - Provider network shared by all tenants
    VLAN - Provider network implemented using 802.1Q tagging
    VXLAN - Provider networks implemented using RFC 7348
    GRE - Provider networks implemented using GRE tunnels
    PORTGROUP - Provider networks implemented for VIO support
    name: segmentation_id, type: UINT32, description: ID of segregated virtual networks
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:nsd/nsr:vld/nsr:provider-network

2.1.1.39.1.1.13  list nsr:placement-groups
  Description
    List of placement groups at NS level
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:nsd/nsr:placement-groups

2.1.1.40.1  list nsr:nsr
  Leaves
    name: ns-instance-config-ref, type: LEAFREF
    name: name-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Network service name reference
    name: nsd-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Network service descriptor id reference
    name: nsd-name-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Network service descriptor name reference
    name: create-time, type: UINT32, description: Creation timestamp of this Network Service.
    The timestamp is expressed as seconds
    since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
    name: instantiated-time, type: UINT32, description: Instantiation timestamp of this Network Service.
    The timestamp is expressed as seconds
    since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: operational status details of NS instance
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of the NS instance
    creating            : The NS is in creation
    created             : The NS has been created
    init                : The NS has just started.
    vl-init-phase       : The VLs in the NS are being instantiated.
    vnf-init-phase      : The VNFs in the NS are being instantiated.
    vnffg-init-phase    : The VNFFGs in the NS are being instantiated.
    running             : The NS is in running state.
    instantiating       : The NS is in instantiating state.
    terminate-rcvd      : The NS terminate received.
    terminate-wait      : The NS is preparing for termination.
    vnffg-terminate-phase : The NS is terminating the VNFFGs in the NS.
    vnf-terminate-phase : The NS is terminating the VNFs in the NS.
    vl-terminate-phase  : The NS is terminating the VLs in the NS.
    terminating         : The NS is in terminating state.
    terminated          : The NS is in the terminated state.
    failed              : The NS instantiation failed.
    failed-temp         : A retriable or continuable Failure
    scaling-out         : The NS is scaling out.
    scaling-in          : The NS is scaling in.
    deleting            : The NS is deleting
    deleted             : The NS has been deleted.
    lcm-in-progress     : The NS heal is in progress.

    name: config-status, type: ENUM, description: The configuration status of the NS instance
    init: Configuration is to be initalized
    configuring: At least one of the VNFs in this instance is in configuring state
    config_not_needed: No config needed for NS
    configured:  All the VNFs in this NS instance are configured or config-not-needed state
    failed: Config failed for NS
    terminate: Config is is terminate phase
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr[nsr:ns-instance-config-ref='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr[nsr:ns-instance-config-ref='STRING']
  Protobuf Type
    .nsr.YangData.RwProject.Project.NsInstanceOpdata.Nsr
  Python Proto-GI Type
    NsrYang.YangData_RwProject_Project_NsInstanceOpdata_Nsr
  C Protobuf-C Struct Type

2.1.1.40.1.1  list nsr:connection-point
  Description
    List for external connection points.
    Each NS has one or more external connection points.
    As the name implies that external connection points
    are used for connecting the NS to other NS or to
    external networks. Each NS exposes these connection
    points to the orchestrator. The orchestrator can
    construct network service chains by connecting the
    connection points between different NS.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the NS connection point.
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr/nsr:connection-point
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr[nsr:ns-instance-config-ref='STRING']/nsr:connection-point[nsr:name='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr/STRING/connection-point/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr/nsr:connection-point
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr[nsr:ns-instance-config-ref='STRING']/nsr:connection-point[nsr:name='STRING']
  Protobuf Type
    .nsr.YangData.RwProject.Project.NsInstanceOpdata.Nsr.ConnectionPoint

2.1.1.40.1.4.1  list nsr:instance
  Description
    Reference to scaling group instance record
  Leaves
    name: instance-id, type: UINT16, description: Scaling group instance id
    name: is-default, type: BOOLEAN, description: Flag indicating whether this instance was part of
    default scaling group (and thus undeletable)
    name: op-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of the NS instance
    init                : The scaling group has just started.
    vnf-init-phase      : The VNFs in the scaling group are being instantiated.
    running             : The scaling group  is in running state.
    terminate           : The scaling group is being terminated.
    vnf-terminate-phase : The VNFs in the scaling group are being terminated.
    terminated          : The scaling group  is in the terminated state.
    failed              : The scaling group instantiation failed.

    name: config-status, type: ENUM, description: The configuration status of the scaling group instance
    configuring : At least one of the VNFs in this scaling group instance
    is in configuring state
    configured  : All the VNFs in this scaling group instance are
    configured or config-not-needed state
    failed      : Configuring this scaling group instance failed

    name: error-msg, type: STRING, description: Reason for failure in configuration of this scaling instance
    name: create-time, type: UINT32, description: Creation timestamp of this scaling group record.
    The timestamp is expressed as seconds
    since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
  XPath Path

    this vnffgr
    name: cloud-account, type: STRING, description: Cloud Account in which NSR is instantiated
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of the VNFFGR instance

    running             : The VNFFGR is in running state.

2.1.1.40.1.6.1  list nsr:task
  Leaves
    name: task-id, type: STRING, description: Task id within a context of a transaction 
    name: state, type: ENUM, description: State of task being executed
    init: Task is being initialized
    running: Task is running
    success: Task has succeeded
    failed: Task has failed
    name: action, type: ENUM, description: Type of task being executed
    status-query  : The task is being queried.
    initial-attempt: Initial attempt of this task
    retry: Task is in retry mode
    rollback: Task is in rollback mode
    cancel: Task is being cancelled
    continue: Task is in continue mode
    name: start-time, type: UINT32, description: Creation timestamp of this LCM operation
    The timestamp is expressed as seconds
    since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
    name: end-time, type: UINT32, description: End timestamp of this LCM operation
    The timestamp is expressed as seconds
    since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
    name: rpc-input, type: STRING, description: Input received for RPC
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr/nsr:last-lcm-record/nsr:task
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr[nsr:ns-instance-config-ref='STRING']/nsr:last-lcm-record/nsr:task[nsr:task-id='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr/STRING/last-lcm-record/task/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr/nsr:last-lcm-record/nsr:task
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr[nsr:ns-instance-config-ref='STRING']/nsr:last-lcm-record/nsr:task[nsr:task-id='STRING']
  Protobuf Type
    .nsr.YangData.RwProject.Project.NsInstanceOpdata.Nsr.LastLcmRecord.Task

    name: default-value, type: STRING, description: The default value for this field
    name: parameter-pool, type: STRING, description: NSD parameter pool name to use for this parameter
    name: read-only, type: BOOLEAN, description: The value should be dimmed by the UI.
    Only applies to parameters with default values.
    name: hidden, type: BOOLEAN, description: The value should be hidden by the UI.
    Only applies to parameters with default values.

2.1.1.40.1.7.3  list nsr:vnf-primitive-group
  Description
    Reference to member-vnf within constituent-vnfds
  Leaves
    name: member-vnf-index-ref, type: UINT64, description: Reference to member-vnf within constituent-vnfds
    name: vnfd-id-ref, type: STRING, description: A reference to a vnfd. This is a
    leafref to path:
    ../../../../nsd:constituent-vnfd
    + [nsd:id = current()/../nsd:id-ref]
    + /nsd:vnfd-id-ref
    NOTE: An issue with confd is preventing the
    use of xpath. Seems to be an issue with leafref
    to leafref, whose target is in a different module.
    Once that is resovled this will switched to use
    leafref
    name: vnfd-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the VNFD
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/nsr:ns-instance-opdata/nsr:nsr/nsr:service-primitive/nsr:vnf-primitive-group

2.1.1.40.1.10.1  container nsr:numeric-constraints
  Leaves
    name: min-value, type: UINT64, description: Minimum value for the parameter

  Leaves

    name: job-status, type: ENUM, description: Job status to be set based on each VNF primitive execution,
    pending  - if at least one VNF is in pending state
    and remaining VNFs are in success state.
    Success  - if all VNF executions are in success state
    failure  - if one of the VNF executions is failure

    name: create-time, type: UINT32, description: Creation timestamp of this Config Agent Job.

    name: job-status-details, type: STRING, description: Config agent job status details, in case of errors

2.1.1.41.1  list rw-oss-bss-account:account
  Description
    OSS/BSS API account configuration.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the OSS/BSS API account.
    name: token-uri, type: STRING, description: Complete URI for obtaining the OAuth2.0 token for using OSS/BSS APIs.
    name: revoke-uri, type: STRING, description: URI where the revoke token request will be sent.
    name: client-id, type: STRING, description: OAuth2.0 client-id for RIFT. OSS/BSS API server should be
    configured with this id to authenticate the RIFT as a client for
    obtaining token.
    name: client-secret, type: STRING, description: OAuth2.0 client-secret for RIFT - acting as cliet for OSS/BSS API.
    name: username, type: STRING, description: Username for obtaining OAuth2.0 access token
    name: password, type: STRING, description: Password of the user for obtaining OAuth2.0 access token
    name: api-server-host, type: UNION, description: Hostname of the OSS/BSS API server.
    name: api-server-port, type: UINT16, description: Port on which the OSS/BSS API server is hosted.

    name: token-status, type: ENUM

    name: token-expires-at, type: STRING, description: Time at which the access token issued by OSS/BSS API server expires.
    name: token-request-attempts, type: UINT64, description: Number of access token request attempts with the OSS/BSS API server.
    name: token-request-success, type: UINT64, description: Number of successfuly access token requests.
    name: token-request-failure, type: UINT64, description: Number of unsuccessful token request attempts.
  XPath Path
